The function can utilize a two-pointer technique, starting from both ends of the sorted list and moving towards the center. 
```python
def two_sum_sorted(xs, target):
    left, right = 0, len(xs) - 1
    while left < right:
        current_sum = xs[left] + xs[right]
        if current_sum == target:
            return (left, right)
        elif current_sum < target:
            left += 1
        else:
            right -= 1
    return None
```
